 with atmosphere evaporated. A smaller but significant second\npopulation (20+\\-10% of all) is necessary to model significantly higher alpha\nvalues, which indicate atmospheres with potentially detectable molecular\nfeatures. We conclude that the atmospheres of small and temperate planets are\nfar from uniformly flat, and that a subset are particularly favorable for\nfollow-up observation from space-based platforms like HST and JWST.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 30 Mar 2018 22:18:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-31"}
